                    <div id="collapse5" class="accordion-body collapse">
                      <div class="accordion-inner">
                        <p>We take a very broad definition of making. Any creative act where you devise and implement an idea falls within the purview of making. Making is as much about the practice of tinkering, playing with available tools and developing your own, as it is about building the end product.</p>
                        <p>Whether the result is thus a set of definitions, a icon-graphic language, a web entity, a physical object, or a friendly robot, you've <em>made</em> it if it came about through an iterative problem solving process where often the biggest challenge was to make everything work together. In sum, Making is ascending above the limitations of what you're given.</p>
                        <p>As long as you believe your project fits that description, it's feasible to deliver over a weekend, and is relevant to Open Data, then it's the perfect project for Make.01.</p>  
